    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 8 with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Yordan Alvarez**, who anchors the day with an elite 87.42 score against Lorenzen. His projection is bolstered by a massive +14% park factor and the optimal #2 spot in the order. Joining him at the top of the efficiency charts are **Junior Caminero** (73.93) and **Kyle Schwarber** (73.53). **Junior Caminero** benefits significantly from a strong 28-PA BvP historical edge against Rea, while **Kyle Schwarber** remains a must-start due to an elite .402 xwOBA and favorable matchup against Mahle. **Caleb Durbin** also grades out as a top-tier play at 69.02; his matchup against the weak Drohan (10.13 xERA) offers the highest SP-skill boost on the board, making him a critical source of potential stolen bases.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the bench, where **Jerar Encarnacion** (42.21) narrowly missed the final slot. While **Jerar Encarnacion** presents a respectable power floor, the optimizer prioritized the higher plate-appearance security and matchup-specific platoon edges offered by **Carson Benge** (46.03). We are monitoring the status of **Victor Scott II** closely; despite his elite speed profile, he is not currently in the projected starting lineup, necessitating his exclusion to protect our limited game caps. \n\nRisk management remains a priority for the middle of our order. **Christian Yelich** (56.92) is our most vulnerable \"Strong\" play; his score is dragged down by the 3.29 xERA of Sonny Gray, and we must be wary of his heavy reliance on platoon advantages to maintain his output. Additionally, while **Colt Keith** (68.36) and **Trea Turner** (69.86) have high scores, both are facing an elite hold pitcher in Ober, which mandates a slight reduction in their stolen base expectations due to the pitcher\u2019s ability to control the running game. We are currently holding **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, and **Luis Pena** on the roster, but their current lack of confirmed lineup spots keeps them firmly on the bench for today's rotation.",
